thread.title: Secret Service says a man shot himself outside of the White House, no other injuries were reported

author: cnbc.com
title: Secret Service says a man shot himself outside of the White House, no other injuries were reported
text:
Secret Service says a man shot himself outside of the White House, no other injuries were reported Published 1 Hour Ago The Associated Press 
The Secret Service says a man shot himself outside the White House, and medical personnel are on the scene. 
President Donald Trump is not at the White House â€” he's in Florida, but is set to return later Saturday. 
The agency says in a Twitter post that there are no other reported injuries related to the incident. 
The Secret Service tweeted about noon Saturday that personnel are responding and a person "allegedly suffered a self-inflicted gun shot wound along the north fence line" of the White House.
